<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4456] Admin UI: Displays dashboard even if Solr is down</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4456</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1. Run Solr and bruing up the Admin dashboard&lt;br/&gt;
2. Stop Solr&lt;br/&gt;
3. Click around the Admin GUI. It apparently works, but displays a spinning wheel for most panels&lt;br/&gt;
4. Click on &quot;Dashboard&quot;. An old cached dashboard is displayed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What should happen is that once connection to Solr is lost, the whole Admin UI displays a large red box &quot;CONNECTION LOST&quot; or something &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
